Four teenagers broke into an aviary and bundled 200 of the animals into sacks and containers around 3.30 am on January 12 .
CCTV showed the men took the birds to a tower block in Walsall , West Midlands and dumped them on the floor .
The birds were also jammed into drawers , squeezed to death and a dog .
Three men and a youth have been convicted of their involvement and will be sentenced next month .